[size=140][u]Simple Hotkeys[/u][/size]

A small, growing collection of simple hotkey actions for X4: Foundations, built on top of the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2181]Native Hotkey API[/url] - every action below is bindable by the player through the native game keybinding UI, just like a vanilla control.

[size=130][u]Overview[/u][/size]

This mod doesn't add any UI of its own. It registers a set of small, focused actions with the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i], which then exposes them on its own [b]Hotkey Management > Hotkey Bindings[/b] page (under Options), where the player assigns the actual physical key through the same native remap UI (and conflict-detection) every other control uses.

Most actions only fire while the player is actually piloting their own ship (no menu open); a couple are map-only instead - see each action's description below for where it applies.

[size=130][u]Requirements[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]X4: Foundations[/b]: Version [b]9.00[/b] or higher.
[*] [b]Native Hotkey API[/b] by Chem O`Dun, version [b]8.00.01[/b] or higher:
[list]
[*] Available on Nexus Mods: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2181]Native Hotkey API[/url]
[*] Available on Steam Workshop: [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3750545906]Native Hotkey API[/url]
[/list]
[*] Indirectly depends on the [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod by kuertee, which is a dependency of the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i]:
[list]
[*] For Game Version [b]8.00HF4[/b] or higher - Version [b]v8.0.4.9[/b] or higher on Nexus Mods: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/552]UI Extensions and HUD[/url]
[*] For Game Version [b]9.00[/b] or higher - Version [b]v9.0.0.6[/b] or higher on Nexus Mods: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/552]UI Extensions and HUD[/url]
[/list]
[/list]
[size=130][u]Installation[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Steam Workshop[/b]: [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3751021954]Native Hotkey API[/url]
[*] [b]Nexus Mods[/b]: [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2183]Simple Hotkeys[/url]
[/list]
[size=130][u]Hotkey Actions[/u][/size]

All of the actions below show up automatically on the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i]'s [b]Hotkey Bindings[/b] page once this mod is enabled - there is nothing to configure here, just assign a key to whichever ones you want to use.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-Simple-Hotkeys/refs/heads/main/docs/images/hotkey_bindings.png[/img][/spoiler]
[list]
[*] [b]Rename Selected/Targeted Object[/b] - opens the vanilla rename popup for the selected (map) or targeted (piloting) object, if it's player-owned.
[*] [b]Follow Target[/b] - engages autopilot to the current target (which tracks a moving target, i.e. "follow"); pressed again on the same target, it disengages autopilot instead.
[*] [b]Eject Illegal Wares[/b] - drops all illegal cargo from the ship's hold and the player's own inventory, based on the local sector's police faction.
[*] [b]Print Combined Skill of Target[/b] - shows a notification with the combined skill of the current target's crew.
[*] [b]Zoom In (Flight Mode)[/b] - piloting only: steps the camera FOV through increasing zoom factors (1x -> 2x -> 4x -> 8x) on repeated presses; pressing again once at the highest factor resets straight back to the FOV that was active before zooming started.
[*] [b]Launch Satellite / Launch Advanced Satellite[/b] - launches a satellite or advanced satellite, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Launch Laser Tower Mk1 / Mk2[/b] - launches a laser tower of the chosen mark, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Launch Mine / Launch Tracker Mine / Launch Friend-or-Foe Mine[/b] - launches the chosen mine type, if one is carried.
[*] [b]Map: Launch ...[/b] - map-only counterpart of every launch action above (Satellite, Advanced Satellite, Laser Tower Mk1/Mk2, Mine, Tracker Mine, Friend-or-Foe Mine), plus [b]Map: Launch Resource Probe[/b] / [b]Map: Launch Navigation Beacon[/b] (no piloting counterpart - vanilla already has hotkeys for those from the ship you're piloting): launches onto the selected player-owned ship on the map instead of the ship you're piloting, if it's carrying one.
[*] [b]Toggle Right Info Panel[/b] - map only: toggles the map's right-side info panel for the current selection, mirroring the existing sidebar icon (there's no vanilla hotkey for either side's info panel, only mouse clicks).
[*] [b]Take Command of Ship (FPS Mode)[/b] - lets you take the pilot/flight-control seat of the ship you're walking in via hotkey, where appropriate "option" is shown on walking crosshair.
[/list]
Please not forget - you can disable any of these actions in appropriate [b]Hotkey Requests[/b] section of the [i]Native Hotkey API[/i]'s menu, if you don't want to use them.

[spoiler][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-Simple-Hotkeys/refs/heads/main/docs/images/hotkey_requests.png[/img][/spoiler]

